de.mrapp.android.adapter

Interface MultipleChoiceExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>

  • Type Parameters:
    GroupType - The type of the underlying data of the adapter's group items
    ChildType - The type of the underlying data of the adapter's child items
    All Superinterfaces:
    Adapter<android.widget.ExpandableListView>, java.lang.Cloneable, DataStructure, EnableStateExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>, ExpandableGridViewAdapter, android.widget.ExpandableListAdapter, ExpandableRecyclerViewAdapter, FilterableExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>, ItemStateExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>, Loggable, Parameterizable, Restorable, SelectableExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>, java.io.Serializable, SortableExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MultipleChoiceExpandableListAdapterImplementation

    public interface MultipleChoiceExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>
extends SelectableExpandableListAdapter<GroupType,ChildType>
    Defines the interface, an adapter, whose underlying data is managed as a list of arbitrary group and child items, of which multiple items can be selected at once, must implement. Such an adapter's purpose is to provide the underlying data for visualization using an ExpandableListView widget.
    Since:
    0.1.0
